Master's Journey

Founder and President – Desi Chargers I created Desi Chargers to build visibility for South Asian grad students. We started rehearsing in dorm lounges and ended up performing and winning iFest 2025. I ran choreography, organized e-board meetings, and mentored every team member, creating something joyful, inclusive, and lasting.

Graduate Assistant – OGISL I was hired my first semester and have since led onboarding for 500+ students, created staff manuals, and helped host Disney trips, trivia nights, and leadership training. I also created evaluation tools and visuals to improve programming engagement.

SHRM Head of Relations & HR Summer Intern In SHRM, I led professional outreach, speaker panels, and student-alumni relations. My summer internship focused on onboarding redesign, psychological safety, and evaluating staff engagement through reflection and documentation.

Research & Innovation I co-led research on Gen Z job satisfaction and leadership styles using MLQ + JSS. I also designed and pitched a start-up idea, ThriveLocal, to help relocated employees connect with their new communities. From branding to surveys, I ran every piece of the concept.

); } export default Masters;
